per classes can be non-public but should stay in their dedicated files.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JUnit class structure**\\n\\nIn JUnit, it seems like I need to check if there's a guideline for one class per file. I notice that existing tests use nested helpers instead of top-level classes. As an alternative, I could dynamically generate bytecode with Javassist, which involves dynamic class generation. I wonder if loading an existing library class with a specific main method would work. Complicating things, I also need to figure out how nested class definitions relate to the NestHost issue, especially since Java compilers have started emitting NestHost info for static nested classes since Java 11. This might impact class loading and access control.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining nested class behavior**\\n\\nIf the main method is public and the class is a public static nested class, I might be able to use `getDeclaredMethod` and invoke it from Viewer, even if that’s a different class loader. I think the nested class should have the ACC_PUBLIC flag, and with top-level class access flags likely set to public too, invoking the method should succeed. However, I notice the dynamically loaded class's main method references a private static final string constant, which could create complications since it doesn’t reference the enclosing class. Perhaps compiling with a source level generating NestHost could help avoid runtime issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering bytecode generation**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using Javassist to generate class bytes directly. It's an active library that supports dynamic class loading and generates bytecode at runtime, which is useful! I don’t think I need any additional resources, but maybe using current dynamic coverage generated by the JVM test with an agent could be beneficial. I should also consider if adding a new file is sufficient, and inspecting the git diff might help clarify any changes needed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Ty7Zi5Wd2D0jknAeeVHFzqW7|fc_072fc9851e5d94ff0169f50a282610819691e9c9fe6b97c45d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist_javassist/ViewerTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1746, "output": 1353, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40987, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777666576535, "responseId": "resp_072fc9851e5d94ff0169f50a10ffa88196aeeb613e02b41e0c"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Ty7Zi5Wd2D0jknAeeVHFzqW7|fc_072fc9851e5d94ff0169f50a282610819691e9c9fe6b97c45d", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "(no output)"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777666600519}]}
